According  to  the  reasoning  of  the 
learned  High  Court  Judge  the  following  facts  can  be

(i) 
According to the evidence of the victim, the 2nd accused had been identified.

(ii) 
However, at the Identification Parade the said victim had, not identified the 1st

(iii) 
There  was  no  evidence  apart  from  the  identification  against  the  1st  accused

(iv) 
Taking  the  above  facts  and  the  law  into  consideration  it  was  decided  by  the
learned  trial  Judge  that  charges  1,  2,  3,  4,  5,  6  and  8  have  not  been  proved
